title: Appointments to Health and Medical Development Advisory Committee
content_text:
p>
	The Government today (October 31) announced the appointment of 15 
	non-official members to the Health and Medical Development Advisory 
	Committee (HMDAC). The appointments will take effect from November 1, 2014 
	for a term of two years. The HMDAC is tasked to advise the Government on the formulation of policies 
	and strategies for the long-term development of medical and health services 
	in Hong Kong.  The Secretary for Food and Health, Dr Ko Wing-man, said, "We have recently

reviewed the role and functions of the HMDAC and decided to re-constitute 
	the Committee as a standing advisory committee to advise the Government on 
	long-term public health and healthcare policy issues, in particular primary 
	care and the rising demand for medical services arising from the ageing 
	population." Dr Ko thanked the members for accepting the appointments. He said, "The 
	membership of the Committee will provide a broad advisory base to assist us 
	in mapping out the long-term development of Hong Kong's healthcare sector

in mapping out the long-term development of Hong Kong's healthcare sector and ways to meet the challenges ahead." Following is the membership list of the Committee as from November 1, 2014: Chairman: Secretary for Food and Health Non-official members:
